            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Add ice, shake & strain",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Mulled wine",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Make your party a simmering success with our complete guide on how to make mulled wine and hot punches",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "There’s something so inviting about the smell of spices mingled with hot wine. Few people can resist it. The rich, warm, faintly exotic steam rising from a pan of mulled wine signifies the start of the festive season more than almost anything else. If you’re planning a party this year, try these recipes: I’ve included old favourites as well as new twists on the traditional. If unexpected guests arrive, they can be easily added to or stretched.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Traditional Spiced Mulled WineMakes 24 glasses or 12 half-pint mugs",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "2 bottles medium or full-bodied red wine (Bulgarian Cabernet Sauvignon is ideal)",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "1.5 litres water1 orange, studded with 10 cloves2 oranges and 2 lemons, sliced",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Rind of the oranges and lemons",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "6 tbsp sugar or honey",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "5cm cinnamon stick",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "2 tbsp fruit liqueur such as cointreau, grand marnier, calvados or cherry brandy",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Mix all the ingredients together in a large saucepan. Heat very gently for about 20 minutes. Do not boil, or you will boil off the alcohol.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Stir gently to ensure that the sugar or honey has dissolved.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Serve with a ladle and keep warm over a low heat.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "troubleshooter",
        "attrs": {
          "intro": "A few of the more common issues, and what tends to fix them.",
          "items": [
            {
              "fix": "Salt a pinch at a time, tasting. A squeeze of lemon or splash of vinegar at the end lifts most savoury dishes.",
              "cause": "Underseasoned or no acid.",
              "symptom": "The dish tastes flat"
            },
            {
              "fix": "Pull off the heat a minute or two before you think it's done. Plate straight away, or transfer to a warmed serving dish.",
              "cause": "Carryover cooking, food keeps cooking on the hot pan after the heat goes off.",
              "symptom": "It's overcooked by the time it reaches the table"
            },
            {
              "fix": "Drop the heat and give it longer. A probe thermometer is the only reliable check for meat.",
              "cause": "Heat too high, browned the outside before the middle warmed through.",
              "symptom": "It's undercooked in the middle"
            },
            {
              "fix": "Reheat covered with a splash of stock or water, on a low heat. Microwave on 60% power if using one, gentler than full blast.",
              "cause": "Reheated uncovered, or no liquid in the pan.",
              "symptom": "The leftovers were dry"
            }
          ],
          "heading": "If something goes wrong"
        }
      },
